cc @alexandrudima 

In order to implement range staging/unstaging, I had to expose the diff algorithm in the API.

```typescript
	export interface LineChange {
		readonly originalStartLineNumber: number;
		readonly originalEndLineNumber: number;
		readonly modifiedStartLineNumber: number;
		readonly modifiedEndLineNumber: number;
	}

	export function computeDiff(oneDocument: TextDocument, otherDocument: TextDocument): Thenable<LineChange[]>;
```

https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/blob/9703537e62075a6c9edd85133c22f601c5f25182/src/vs/vscode.proposed.d.ts#L158-L165

I'm not entirely happy as to how that looks like.

@jrieken Do you have any ideas how we can improve this? Maybe we could add it to the `workspace` namespace, since it computes diffs on TextDocuments.

* In TMSyntax.ts
* around `this._themeService.onDidColorThemeChange((e) => this._updateTheme());`
* replace with:

```
		this._themeService.onDidColorThemeChange((e) => {
			console.log('RECEIVED COLOR THEME CHANGED EVENT');
			console.log(JSON.stringify(this._themeService.getColorTheme().settings));
			this._updateTheme();
		});
```

Start dev instance. Observe event being fired 3 times on startup even if it always returns the same color theme. This is unexpected and causes tokenization to start and stop 3 times during startup. This was not the behaviour of the theme service e.g. 3 weeks ago.
